  "prompt": "Is it okay for an Indian to travel from USA to India via Brussels with expired US visa?",
  "response": "Traveling with an expired visa can be complicated and can pose problems. Here are a few important points to consider:\n\n1. **Validity of the US Visa:** If your US visa has expired, you may face issues when attempting to re-enter the USA after visiting India.\n\n2. **Visa for Transit:** While transiting through Brussels, you need to check if you require a transit visa for Belgium. Indian citizens might need a transit visa depending on the length of the layover and the conditions in Belgium.\n\n3. **Entry into India:** The expired US visa does not affect your entry into India, as you are a citizen of India.\n\n4. **Re-entry to the USA:** For re-entry into the USA, you'll need a valid visa. If your visa is expired, you will need to apply for a new one before returning.\n\nYou should consult the embassy or consulate for precise guidelines and regulations related to your situation.",
